  "body": "### Description\nTo make it easier for users to use checkpoint sync, automatically detect when the URL given to --initial-state is the root of a beacon node REST API and automatically append `/eth/v2/debug/beacon/states/finalized`\n\nThe right approach here is probably to request the root URL and if it is an error response or not application/octet-stream then log an info message and try with the additional path.\n\nI'd be tempted to restrict this to when the supplied URL has no path (or just `/`) to avoid having it kick in because of a typo in the provided URL or something like that.  So `https://example.com` and `https://example.com/` would have the path added but `https://example.com/someting/` wouldn't.",
