    "body": "No it doesn't always end with that. That's the most common path because that's the path to get the latest finalized state in the standard REST API.  But I could put a state file anywhere and point to it - it doesn't have to come directly from the standard REST API.  For example before Infura provided an endpoint, I used to periodically shove states in https://github.com/ajsutton/eth2-states so people could use them for checkpoint sync.",
